# Garlic Mashed Cauliflower

> #vegetable #side

![](6EFCDF19-6B15-4282-99A0-79A2EB095D97.jpg)

Set a stockpot of water to boil over high heat.

- Cauliflower | 1, medium | 
- Cream Cheese | 1 tbsp | Softened

Clean and cut cauliflower into small pieces. Cook in boiling water for about 6 minutes, or until well done. Drain well; do not let cool and pat cooked cauliflower very dry between several layers of paper towels.

- Parmesan | 1/4 cup | Grated
- Garlic | 1/2 tsp | Minced
- Salt | 1/2 tsp | 

In a bowl with an immersion blender, or in a food processor, puree the hot cauliflower with the cream cheese, Parmesan, garlic, salt, and pepper until almost smooth.

- Pepper | 1/8 teaspoon freshly ground black | 
- Chives | 1/2 teaspoon chopped fresh or dry for garnish | 
- Butter | 3 tablespoons unsalted | 

## Directions

Garnish with chives, and serve hot with pats of butter.
